<p>
  If you’ve been around the Raleigh/Durham/Chapel Hill area, you’ve probably heard <a href="https://twitter.com/startuphats">David Gardner</a>’s name pop up from time to time. David is a local Triangle investor who has been an entrepreneur most of his life. He has started 7 companies and had 6 successful exits in a row between $12m and $100m per exit. Last year, he started Cofounder’s Capital to bet on more Triangle startups.
</p>

<p>
  We asked Dave to give us some tips on being a successful entrepreneur and investor. Here’s a bit about Dave and a few tips that come along with.
</p>

