<h4 class="margin-top">
  You started Cofounders Capital last year to invest in local Triangle startups. How did that come about?
</h4>

<p>
  “Since I’ve had such a great track record, other investors wanted to get involved in that. Last year, a bunch of people wanted to invest with me, so I put together a $12m seed fund. The size of investments I make are $300k, and I am managing that fund now.”
</p>

<p>
  David has done 6 investments out of that fund. He keeps a straight forward model of investing in mostly software and IP focused startups.
</p>

<p>
  “B2B is my sweet spot. Products that we can sell to large customers who can write big checks.” says David.
</p>

